HEADWORD: Borderer
<hw>Bor"der*er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who dwells on
a border, or at the extreme part or confines of a country, region, or
tract of land; one who dwells near to a place or region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Borderers</qex> of the Caspian.</q>
<rj><qau>Dyer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bordland</ent>⟦br⟧
